 over heat to de-glaze the pan. Turn off heat and allow pan to cool on stove top."},{"content":"Arrange asparagus and carrot around seared lamb in Varoma dish and on Varoma tray, then place Varoma into position and cook <b>4 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Lamb will be cooked medium-rare. If desired, continue cooking until lamb, asparagus, carrots and potatoes are cooked to your preference."},{"content":"Transfer lamb, asparagus, carrots and potatoes into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to rest and keep warm. The lamb will continue to cook as it rests. Retain stock in mixing bowl."},{"content":"In a ceramic or glass bowl, combine whisky and cornflour together, then set aside."},{"content":"Add remaining 1 tsp peppercorns, cream, reserved pan juices and reserved whisky and cornflour mixture to stock in mixing bowl and reduce <b>10-12 min\/90°C\/\/speed <b>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>."},{"content":"Slice lamb and serve with potatoes, carrots and asparagus, drizzled with pink peppercorn sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or the<em> Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Meat stock paste recipe.","Pink peppercorns can be sourced at specialty grocery stores."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","30m","4 portions"]}